ian film producers]]\n[[Category:Chinese male film actors]]\n[[Category:Chinese film directors]]\n[[Category:Taiwanese people from Shanghai]]\n", "name_user": "Rqiang84", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jimmy_Wang_Yu"}
{"title_page": "Somerset County, Maine", "text_new": "{{short description|County in Maine, US}}\n{{Infobox U.S. county\n| county = Somerset County\n| state = Maine\n| seal =\n| founded date =\n| founded year = 1809\n| seat wl = Skowhegan\n| largest city wl = Skowhegan\n| city type = town\n| area_total_sq_mi = 4094\n| area_land_sq_mi = 3924\n| area_water_sq_mi = 169\n| area percentage = 4.1%\n| population_as_of = 2010\n| population_total = 52228\n| pop_est_as_of = 2019\n| population_est = 50,484\n| population_density_sq_mi = auto\n| named for = [[Somerset]] County, England\n| web = http://somersetcounty-me.org/\n| ex image = Courthouse, Skowhegan, ME.jpg\n| ex image cap = Somerset County Courthouse\n| district = 2nd\n| time zone = Eastern\n}}\n\n'''Somerset County''' is a [[County (United States)|county]] in the [[U.S. state|state]] of [[Maine]], in the [[United States]]. As of the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]], the population was 52,228.<ref name=\"QF\">{{cite web|title=State & County QuickFacts|url=http://quickfacts.census.gov/qfd/states/23/23025.html|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=August 19, 2013}}</ref>  Its [[county seat]] is [[Skowhegan, Maine|Skowhegan]].<ref name=\"GR6\">{{cite web|url=http://www.naco.org/Counties/Pages/FindACounty.aspx|accessdate=2011-06-07|title=Find a County|publisher=National Association of Counties}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nSomerset County was established on March 1, 1809<ref>{{cite book | last=Seltzer | first=Leon Eugene | title=The Columbia Lippincott gazetteer of the world | url=https://archive.org/details/columbialippinco00selt | url-access=registration | publisher=Columbia Univ. Pr. | year=1952 | isbn=0-231-01559-3 | oclc=299604592 | page=[https://archive.org/details/columbialippinco00selt/page/1794 1794]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://history.rays-place.com/me/somerset-cty-me.htm|title=History of Somerset County, Maine|website=history.rays-place.com|access-date=2009-01-25}}{{dead link|date=April 2020|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> from portions of [[Kennebec County, Maine|Kennebec County]] and was named after [[Somerset, England|Somerset County in England]].<ref>{{cite news | url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=3aQgAAAAIBAJ&sjid=FWkFAAAAIBAJ&pg=1463%2C5719635 | title=Some Maine town names | work=The Lewiston Daily Sun | date=Jun 13, 1928 | accessdate=17 October 2015 | author=Yates, Edgar A.P. | pages=4}}</ref> Its most famous resident is Lorne Lynn Armstrong.\n\n== Government and politics ==\nSomerset County is part of [[Maine's 2nd congressional district]].\n\nIn 1992, Somerset County was one of three counties in the state (the others being [[Knox County, Maine|Knox]] and [[Piscataquis County, Maine|Piscataquis]]) where [[Ross Perot]] received over 38% of the vote and won.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://uselectionatlas.org/RESULTS/stats.php?year=1992&f=1&off=0&elect=0|title=1992 Presidential Election Statistics}}</ref> In 2008, [[Barack Obama]] received 51.9% of the vote.<ref>{{cite web | title=President Map \u2013 Election Results 2008 | website=The New York Times | date=2008-12-09 | url=https://www.nytimes.com/elections/2008/results/president/map.html?scp=1&sq=%22election+map&st=cse | access-date=2019-09-05}}</ref>\n\n=== Voter registration ===\n{| class=wikitable\n! colspan = 6 | Voter registration and party enrollment as of May 2019 {{update after|2021|1|7|reason=Data from general elections is typically reported on the Bureau's website during the first week of the following January}}<ref>{{cite web |author1=Bureau of Corporations, Elections & Commissions |title=Registered & Enrolled Voters - Statewide |url=https://www.maine.gov/sos/cec/elec/data/data-pdf/r-e-active.pdf |format=PDF |publisher=Department of the [[Secretary of State of Maine|Secretary of State]], [[State of Maine]] |accessdate=13 November 2019 |page=26 |date=5 May 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n{{party color|Independent Party (United States)}}\n| Unenrolled\n| align = center | {{formatnum: 1339