2,770''\n|  style=\"background:honeyDew;\"|3.0% ''289''\n|-\n|  {{Party shading/Republican}}|'''[[United States presidential election in Maine, 1916|1916]]'''\n|  {{Party shading/Republican}}|'''51.2%''' ''3,567''\n|  {{Party shading/Democratic}}|45.0% ''3,134''\n|  style=\"background:honeyDew;\"|3.7% ''260''\n|-\n|  {{Party shading/Progressive}}|'''[[United States presidential election in Maine, 1912|1912]]'''\n|  {{Party shading/Republican}}|19.4% ''1,235''\n|  {{Party shading/Democratic}}|36.5% ''2,317''\n|  style=\"background:honeyDew;\"|'''44.1%''' ''2,804''\n|-\n|  {{Party shading/Republican}}|'''[[United States presidential election in Maine, 1908|1908]]'''\n|  {{Party shading/Republican}}|'''65.3%''' ''3,688''\n|  {{Party shading/Democratic}}|29.7% ''1,676''\n|  style=\"background:honeyDew;\"|5.0% ''284''\n|}\n{{Hidden end}}\n\n== Geography ==\nAccording to the [[U.S. Census Bureau]], the county has a total area of {{convert|4094|sqmi}}, of which {{convert|3924|sqmi}} is land and {{convert|169|sqmi}} (4.1%) is water.<ref name=\"GR1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/geo/maps-data/data/docs/gazetteer/counties_list_23.txt|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=September 7, 2014|date=August 22, 2012|title=2010 Census Gazetteer Files|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140909034104/http://www.census.gov/geo/maps-data/data/docs/gazetteer/counties_list_23.txt|archivedate=September 9, 2014}}</ref> It is the third-largest county in Maine by area.\n\n=== Mountains ===\n* [[Boundary Bald Mountain]]\n* [[Coburn Mountain (Maine)|Coburn Mountain]]\n* [[Mount Bigelow (Maine)|Mount Bigelow]]\n* [[Moxie Mountain]]\n* [[Sandy Bay Mountain]]\n\n=== Bodies of water ===\n* [[Carrabassett River]]\n* [[Flagstaff Lake (Maine)|Flagstaff Lake]]\n* [[Kennebec River]]\n* [[Moose River, Maine|Moose River]]\n* [[Moxie Falls]]\n\n=== Major highways ===\n{{div col}}\n* [[Maine State Route 6]]\n* [[Maine State Route 8]]\n* [[Maine State Route 11]]\n* [[Maine State Route 16]]\n* [[Maine State Route 27]]\n* [[Maine State Route 100]]\n* [[Maine State Route 137]]\n* [[U.S. Route 201]]\n** [[Armstrong-Jackman Border Crossing]]\n* [[U.S. Route 201A]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n=== Adjacent counties and municipalities ===\n{{div col}}\n* [[Aroostook County, Maine|Aroostook County]] \u2013 north\n* [[Penobscot County, Maine|Penobscot County]] \u2013 east\n* [[Piscataquis County, Maine|Piscataquis County]] \u2013 east\n* [[Waldo County, Maine|Waldo County]] \u2013 southeast\n* [[Kennebec County, Maine|Kennebec County]] \u2013 south\n* [[Franklin County, Maine|Franklin County]] \u2013 southwest\n* [[Le Granit Regional County Municipality, Quebec]] \u2013 west\n* [[Beauce-Sartigan Regional County Municipality, Quebec]] \u2013 west\n* [[Les Etchemins Regional County Municipality, Quebec]] \u2013 northwest\n* [[Montmagny Regional County Municipality, Quebec]] \u2013 northwest\n{{div col end}}\n\nSomerset County is one of few counties in the United States to border ten counties and county equivalents.\n\n== Demographics ==\n{{US Census population\n|1810= 12910\n|1820= 21787\n|1830= 35787\n|1840= 33912\n|1850= 35581\n|1860= 36753\n|1870= 34611\n|1880= 32333\n|1890= 32627\n|1900= 33849\n|1910= 36301\n|1920= 37171\n|1930= 39111\n|1940= 38245\n|1950= 39785\n|1960= 39749\n|1970= 40597\n|1980= 45028\n|1990= 49767\n|2000= 50888\n|2010= 52228\n|estyear=2019\n|estimate=50484\n|estref=<ref name=\"USCensusEst2018\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/popest/data/tables.2018.html|title=Population and Housing Unit Estimates|accessdate=July 31, 2019}}</ref>\n|align-fn=center\n|footnote=U.S. Decennial Census<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/prod/www/decennial.html|title=U.S. Decennial Census|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=September 7, 2014}}</ref><br />1790\u20131960<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mapserver.lib.virginia.edu|title=Historical Census Browser|publisher=University of Virginia Library|accessdate=September 7, 2014}}</ref> 1900\u20131990<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/population/cencounts/me190090.txt|title=Population of Counties by Decennial Census: 1900 to 1990|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=September 7, 2014}}</ref><br />1990\u20132000<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/population/www/cen2000/briefs/phc-t4/tables/tab02.pdf|title=Census 2000 PHC-T-4. Ranking Tables for Counties: 1990 and 2000|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=September 7, 2014}}</ref> 2010\u20132016<ref name=\"QF\" />\n}}\n\n=== 2000 census ===\nAs of the [[census]]<ref name=\"GR2\">{{cite web|url=http://factfinder.census.gov|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200212221153/http://factfinder.census.gov/main.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=2020-02-12|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2008-01-31|title=American FactFinder}}</ref> of 2000, there were 50,888 people, 20,496 households, and 14,121 families living in the county.  The [[population density]] was 13 people per square mile (5/km\u00b2).  There were 28,222 housing units at an average density of 7 per square&nbsp;mile (3/km\u00b2).  The racial makeup of the county was 98.00% [[Race (United States Census)|White]], 0.24% [[Race (United States Census)|Black]] or [[Race (United States Census)|African American]], 0.41% [[Race (United States Census)|Native American]], 0.34% [[Race (United States Census)|Asian]], 0.02% [[Race (United States Census)|Pacific Islander]], 0.11% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 0.89% from two or more races.  0.46% of the population were [[Race (United States Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Race (United States Census)|Latino]] of any race. 20.9% were of [[English people|English]], 17.7% [[French people|French]], 15.1% [[United States]] or American, 11.5% [[Irish people|Irish]] and 8.8% [[French Canadian]] ancestry. 96.2% spoke [[English language|English]] and 2.9% [[French language|French]] as their first language.\n\nThere were 20,496 households out of which 31.60% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 54.20% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 10.10% had a female householder with no husband present, and 31.10% were non-families. 24.60% of all households were made up of individuals and 10.20% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.  The average household size was 2.44 and the average family size was 2.87.\n\nIn the county, the population was spread out with 24.70% under the age of 18, 7.00% from 18 to 24, 28.70% from 25 to 44, 25.30% from 45 to 64, and 14.30% who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 39 years. For every 100 females there were 96.00 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 93.30 males.\n\nThe median income for a household in the county was $30,731, and the median income for a family was $36,464. Males had a median income of $29,032 versus $20,745 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the county was $15,474.  About 11.10% of families and 14.90% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 19.40% of those under age 18 and 12.50% of those age 65 or over.\n\n=== 2010 census ===\nAs of the [[2010 United States Census]], there were 52,228&nbsp;people, 21,927&nbsp;households, and 14,353&nbsp;families living in the county.<ref name=\"census-dp1\">{{cite web\n  |url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/0500000US23025\n  |title=DP-1 Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics: 2010 Demographic Profile Data\n  |accessdate=2016-01-21\n  |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]\n  |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213034530/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/0500000US23025\n  |archive-date=2020-02-13\n  |url-status=dead\n  }}</ref> The population density was {{convert|13.3|PD/sqmi}}. There were 30,569 housing units at an average density of {{convert|7.8|/sqmi}}.<ref name=\"census-density\">{{cite web\n  |url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/GCTPH1.CY07/0500000US23025\n  |accessdate=2016-01-21\n  |title=Population, Housing Units, Area, and Density: 2010 \u2013 County\n  |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]\n  |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213184650/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/GCTPH1.CY07/0500000US23025\n  |archive-date=2020-02-13\n  |url-status=dead\n  }}</ref> The racial makeup of the county was 97.1% white, 0.6% Asian, 0.5% American Indian, 0.4% black or African American, 0.1% from other races, and 1.3% from two or more races. Those of Hispanic or Latino origin made up 0.8% of the population.<ref name=\"census-dp1\" /> In terms of ancestry, 25.1% were [[French Americans|French]], 24.2% were [[English Americans|English]], 15.8% were [[Irish people|Irish]], 8.0% were [[Germans|German]], 7.9% were [[Americans|American]], and 6.1% were [[French Canadian]].<ref name=\"census-dp2\">{{cite web\n  |url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/10_5YR/DP02/0500000US23025\n  |title=DP02 SELECTED SOCIAL CHARACTERISTICS IN THE UNITED STATES \u2013 2006\u20132010 American Community Survey 5-Year Estimates\n  |accessdate=2016-01-21\n  |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]\n  |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213021230/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/10_5YR/DP02/0500000US23025\n  |archive-date=2020-02-13\n  |url-status=dead\n  }}</ref>\n\nOf the 21,927&nbsp;households, 28.2% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 49.7% were married couples living together, 10.3% had a female householder with no husband present, 34.5% were non-families, and 26.9% of all households were made up of individuals. The average household size was 2.35 and the average family size was 2.80. The median age was 43.6 years.<ref name=\"census-dp1\" />\n\nThe median income for a household in the county was $36,647 and the median income for a family was $47,177. Males had a median income of $41,235 versus $30,029 for females. The per capita income for the county was $20,709. About 14.0% of families and 18.4% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 25.0% of those under age 18 and 12.7% of those age 65 or over.<ref name=\"census-dp3\">{{cite web\n  |url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/10_5YR/DP03/0500000US23025\n  |title=DP03 SELECTED ECONOMIC CHARACTERISTICS \u2013 2006\u20132010 American Community Survey 5-Year Estimates\n  |accessdate=2016-01-21\n  |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]\n  |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213014233/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/ACS/10_5YR/DP03/0500000US23025\n  |archive-date=2020-02-13\n  |url-status=dead\n  }}</ref>\n\n== Education ==\n\n=== School administrative districts ===\nThe following school districts are located at least partly in Somerset County:<ref>{{cite web | access-date=2019-09-05 | url=https://www.maine.gov/doe/sites/maine.gov.doe/files/inline-files/SAUsbyTypewithCostSharingJULY2018_RSU_forFY19_updated03Aug2018_1.pdf | title=Regional School Units In Maine | website=Maine.gov}}</ref>\n* [[MSAD 4]]\n* [[MSAD 12]]\n* [[MSAD 13]]\n* [[MSAD 49]]\n* [[MSAD 53]]\n* [[MSAD 54]]\n* [[MSAD 59]]\n* [[MSAD 74]]\n\n=== Secondary schools ===\n* [[Carrabec High School]] \u2013 North Anson<ref>{{cite web | title=Carrabec High School | website=Carrabec High School | date=2019-08-07 | url=http://chs.carrabec.org/ | access-date=2019-09-05}}</ref>\n* [[Faith Baptist Christian School]] \u2013 Skowhegan (serves multiple grades)<ref>{{cite web | title=Explore Faith Baptist Christian School in Skowhegan, ME | website=GreatSchools.org | url=https://www.greatschools.org/maine/skowhegan/804-Faith-Baptist-Christian-School/ | access-date=2019-09-05}}</ref>\n* [[Forest Hills Consolidated School]] (K-12) \u2013 Jackman<ref>{{cite web | title=Forest Hills School | website=Forest Hills School | date=2019-07-31 | url=http://www.sad12.org/ | access-date=2019-09-05}}</ref>\n* [[Lawrence High School (Maine)|Lawrence High School]] \u2013 Fairfield<ref>{{cite web | title=Lawrence High School, Fairfield, Maine USA | website=Facebook | url=https://www.facebook.com/lawrencehighschoolfairfieldmaineusa/ | access-date=2019-09-05}}</ref>\n* [[Madison Area Memorial High School]] \u2013 Madison<ref>{{cite web | title=Home | website=Madison Area Memorial High School | date=2019-06-15 | url=https://www.sad59.k12.me.us/high | access-date=2019-09-05}}</ref>\n* [[Maine Academy of Natural Sciences]] \u2013 [[Fairfield, Maine|Hinckley]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gwh.org/|title=Good Will Hinckley/Maine Academy of Natural Sciences/United States|website=goodwillhinckley}}</ref>\n* [[Maine Central Institute]] \u2013 Pittsfield<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mci-school.org/index.cfm|title=Maine Central Institute website|access-date=2010-10-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141030001243/http://www.mci-school.org/index.cfm|archive-date=2014-10-30|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* [[Skowhegan Area High School]] \u2013 Skowhegan<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sahs.msad54.org/|title=Home|website=RSU/MSAD 54}}</ref>\n* [[Upper Kennebec Valley Memorial High School]] \u2013 Bingham<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sad13.org/|title=sad13|last=|first=|date=|website=sad13.org|language=en|access-date=2019-09-05}}</ref>\n\n=== Higher education ===\n* [[Kennebec Valley Community College]]\n\n=== Miscellaneous ===\n* [[Skowhegan School of Painting and Sculpture]]\n* L.C. Bates Museum\n\n== Communities ==\n\n=== Towns ===\n{{div col|colwidth=12em}}\n* [[Anson, Maine|Anson]]\n* [[Athens, Maine|Athens]]\n* [[Bingham, Maine|Bingham]]\n* [[Cambridge, Maine|Cambridge]]\n* [[Canaan, Maine|Canaan]]\n* [[Caratunk, Maine|Caratunk]]\n* [[Cornville, Maine|Cornville]]\n* [[Detroit, Maine|Detroit]]\n* [[Embden, Maine|Embden]]\n* [[Fairfield, Maine|Fairfield]]\n* [[Harmony, Maine|Harmony]]\n* [[Hartland, Maine|Hartland]]\n* [[Jackman, Maine|Jackman]]\n* [[Madison, Maine|Madison]]\n* [[Mercer, Maine|Me